			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ender's Game Trailer Released
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1780991">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							My only real complaint is that they don't make it clear that this is all a training program. The trailer makes it look like he is commanding real warships. I think it could give people the wrong idea, and potentially ruin part of the point of the book. Everything else looks much better than I expected, but I still wonder if they can do this right.<br />
<br />
I also assume the atmosphere stuff is supposed to depict the first contact. It's wrong, but I get the feeling they did it this way to make it easier to understand for audiences. Probably also translates better in a visual medium.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
		<div class="postfoot">
