				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ender's Game Trailer Released
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1789602">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Guys, remember that a short 1:30 trailer has a very specific purpose. Even the trailer for Gravity, which by all accounts should be a thought provoking film, resembled some kind of cheesy action-thriller more than anything else.<br />
<br />
Most of my opinions haven't changed, a couple good things, a couple bad things.<br />
<br />
-Good Things: <br />
<br />
Production values and performances still look great. And by production values I just don't mean spaceships and explosions, pew pew pew. The sets and costumes are also really good. With the exception of the atmospheric dogfight, everything looks like it came right out of the book. <br />
<br />
-Bad Things:<br />
<br />
So this trailer makes it look like the aliens really did attack the earth? Bleh. <br />
The trailer is <b>still</b> ruining the plot, and making it look like a genuine war instead of simulations. I guess it's not exciting to say &quot;come watch this movie about someone training to fight a war&quot;.<br />
<br />
<br />
I'm going to keep giving them the benefit of the doubt. I think it could be good, and I think it will actually turn on a few brains in the audience and get them thinking about what they just watched.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
