				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ender's Game Trailer Released
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1789668">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Unless this film has a gigantic zero-G arena in which a thousand boys at a time fight with their bare hands and feet over a flag daily until all the surviving boys have an innate grasp of realtime 3d tactics because they are slated to man the newly-built fleet in the next great battle against an alien foe, then this movie will have missed the mark by about a parsec.  The simulators came much later.  Their training took years.  This film should indicate that if it means to convey anything from the book.  And let's not ever forget the overwhelming drumbeat of propaganda the boys faced about their duty, duty, duty, duty.  The book was built around this certain framework, and should not be turned into a glorification of martial prowess via epic space battles.  The actual space battle in the book was short and technical and made Ender feel so shitty that Card had to write three more books to deal with the results.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
