			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ender's Game Trailer Released
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1789669">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The trailer did have a clip of the zero G arena, although being a movie I'm sure it will fast forward through most of the displayed plot points.<br />
<br />
My impression of the space battles in the books were that they were epic chess matches where Ender used his intelligence to devise ingenious strategies. There was plenty of room for cool special effects and still be accurate to the source material.<br />
<br />
Edit: I remember in the Gravity thread, Ppatty pointed out that I was being condescending in saying that your average movie goer (&quot;normal&quot; people by my own words) can't appreciate a certain type of &quot;smart&quot; movie, but I think Ender's Game is one of those that can actually reach out to those sort of people while still providing the opportunity for worthwhile retrospection and thought. Which is why I am defending it. It's like a gateway drug to a wider world of science fiction. You go for the space battles, and leave realizing that it was more interesting than you thought it would be.<br />
<br />
Hopefully. If they don't ruin it, which I admit they might. <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" />
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
