			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ender's Game Trailer Released
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1789844">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I read something online somewhere (maybe Uberhumor, I don't remember) that went something like this:<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				Girl #1 and Girl #2 go up to Author at a book signing.<br />
Girl #2 nudges Girl #1 and says &quot;Ask him.&quot;<br />
Author says &quot;Ask him what?&quot;<br />
Girl #1 speaks up and says, &quot;Our professor, when he was teaching us your book, said that you described the main character's room as blue because you wanted to signify the character's loneliness and solitude.  Would you agree?&quot;<br />
<br />
Author paused for a minute and replied, &quot;The character's room is blue, because I happen to like blue.  Also, your professor is full of shit.&quot;
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Whether that's true or not, I dunno, but it makes me wonder if he truly wanted his book to be &quot;smart and introspective&quot; other than to write something that kids might dream/fantasize about even before hearing about this book - what would happen if my actions in a video game were actually really affecting someone? - and simply enjoyed writing it.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
